reviews.text: Very rude lady in the ticket booth. It doesn't cost much to smile.

The woman that sells you tickets has to be the most miserable human being in this world. I don't know if she has a severe hate for everything or just likes to communicate in small short grunts. 
Me: hi good morning can I have a ticket to Cambridge
Woman: grunt and pointing to card machines
Card machine: thank you very much
Me:Thank you
Woman: grunt.

Very handy to get to London/Stratford/Bishop's Stortford/Cambridge although it is served by two trains an hour and they all stop at all stops so its slow. Car park is always available. Staffing is sporadic and you do get the impression its not the greatest place for them to work. Smells of wee on a Saturday/Sunday.
After a long wait to get served, I had an enjoyable meal and the staff were attentive even though it was very busy. Top marks
A platform in a industrial area and that’s all
